---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="Terms of Service — Flynt AI"
  description="Flynt AI LLC Terms of Service — the terms governing your use of the Flynt platform."
>

<div class="legal-page">

  <section class="legal-hero">
    <div class="legal-container">
      <div class="tag">Legal</div>
      <h1>Terms of Service</h1>
      <p class="legal-meta">Last updated: [INSERT DATE] &nbsp;·&nbsp; Have legal counsel review before publishing.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="legal-content">
    <div class="legal-container">
      <div class="legal-body">

        <p class="legal-intro">Please read these Terms of Service ("Terms") carefully before using the Flynt platform and website operated by Flynt AI LLC ("Flynt", "we", "us"). By accessing or using the Service, you agree to be bound by these Terms. If you do not agree, do not use the Service.</p>

        <div class="legal-section">
          <h2>1. The Service</h2>
          <p>Flynt provides an AI-powered client acquisition research platform that automates the identification and delivery of prospect accounts, decision-maker information, and market signals (the "Service"). The Service is intended for business use by professionals engaged in revenue generation, client acquisition, and business development.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="legal-section">
          <h2>2. Eligibility</h2>
          <p>You must be at least 18 years old and have the legal capacity to enter into a binding agreement to use the Service. By creating an account, you represent that all registration information you provide is accurate and that you will keep it current.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="legal-section">
          <h2>3. Accounts and Access</h2>
          <p>You are responsible for maintaining the confidentiality of your account credentials and for all activity that occurs under your account. Notify us immediately at <a href="mailto:info@tryflynt.ai">info@tryflynt.ai</a> if you suspect unauthorised access. We reserve the right to suspend or terminate accounts that violate these Terms.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="legal-section">
          <h2>4. Subscriptions and Billing</h2>
          <p>Flynt is offered on a monthly subscription basis. Fees are charged at the start of each billing period.</p>
          <ul>
            <li>All fees are non-refundable except where required by law.</li>
            <li>You may cancel your subscription at any time. Cancellation takes effect at the end of the current billing period; you retain access until that date.</li>
            <li>We reserve the right to modify pricing with 30 days' notice. Continued use after the effective date constitutes acceptance of the new pricing.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="legal-section">
          <h2>5. Acceptable Use</h2>
          <p>You agree not to use the Service to:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>Violate any applicable law or regulation</li>
            <li>Harvest or collect data in ways that violate the terms of third-party platforms</li>
            <li>Send unsolicited bulk communications ("spam") using intelligence delivered by Flynt</li>
            <li>Misrepresent your identity or affiliation in outreach based on Flynt data</li>
            <li>Reverse engineer, decompile, or attempt to extract the source code of the platform</li>
            <li>Resell, sublicense, or otherwise commercialise Flynt's outputs without our written consent</li>
          </ul>
          <p>We reserve the right to terminate access for any user found in violation of these provisions.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="legal-section">
          <h2>6. Intellectual Property</h2>
          <p>All intellectual property rights in the Service, including its software, design, and methodology, belong to Flynt AI LLC. Your subscription grants you a limited, non-exclusive, non-transferable licence to access and use the Service for your internal business purposes. You retain ownership of the targeting configurations and business data you provide.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="legal-section">
          <h2>7. Data and Outputs</h2>
          <p>Flynt delivers research outputs and lead intelligence based on publicly available data and AI processing. We make reasonable efforts to ensure accuracy but do not warrant that outputs are complete, error-free, or up to date. You are responsible for verifying information and complying with applicable laws (including data protection and anti-spam regulations) when acting on Flynt's outputs.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="legal-section">
          <h2>8. No Guarantee of Results</h2>
          <p>Flynt provides research and intelligence infrastructure. We do not guarantee that use of the Service will result in new clients, revenue, leads, or any specific business outcome. Results depend entirely on your targeting, messaging, follow-up, and execution. Flynt prepares opportunity — your team converts it.</p>
        </div>

